id:
This form will help your building captains keep track of the issues in your apartment and the 311 complaints you make. 

If you have already called 311, or call while filling out this form, remember to write down the 311 ""Service Request Number"" they give you. If you call 311 after filling out this form, we'll send you a follow up text message that you can respond to with your 311 Service Request Number.

If you need to change any answers in the form, you can go 'back' at any time by hitting the 'up' arrow in the bottom right corner of the form on your computer, or the 'back' arrow on mobile.

Your responses will be kept private and will only visible to UPT organizers and to JustFix.org â€” the nonprofit organization assisting UPT with this campaign.

If you have already submitted 311 complaints, share the Service Request Number they gave you so we can monitor the status. The complaint number will be formatted like: "311-12345678". 

If you do not yet have a Service Request Number, you can still hit the "Submit" button below. After you make your complaint to 311, we will follow up with a text message in a couple days to ask you for the Service Request Number.

You can enter up to 10 Service Request Numbers through this form. If you have more than 10, you can let us know in the follow up text chain.

We'll send you a text message now with a checklist of all the issues you selected. You can refer to that list when HPD inspectors come to make sure that they issue violations for all issues.

We will send you a text message in a few days to check on the status of your 311 complaint and to learn if HPD issued violations or if you need to call 311 again.
